01-cvis-ecosystem-overview
Healthcare IT Cardiology Informatics Consultant Readiness Curriculum
Module 1: EHR Ecosystem Foundation | Lesson 1.1

üìå Overview
This lesson establishes the architectural and market foundation for understanding cardiovascular information systems (CVIS) within modern healthcare IT environments. Through systematic analysis of vendor positioning, standards frameworks, and integration patterns, you'll develop the consultant's mental model for assessing any cardiology IT environment.
Learning Outcome: Move from "which system is better" thinking to contextual architectural assessment‚Äîthe cornerstone of consulting expertise.

üéØ What You'll Learn
Core Concepts

CVIS fundamental distinction: Data-centric integration philosophy vs. image-focused PACS
Three-tier architecture model: Enterprise EHR ‚Üí Department CVIS ‚Üí Modality devices
Market landscape: Epic Cupid dominance, Cerner challenges, hybrid architecture patterns
Standards ecosystem: HL7, DICOM, IHE as interoperability tools (not just compliance)
Consultant assessment frameworks: Diagnostic questions for organizational readiness evaluation

Why This Matters for Cardiovascular IT Consultants
