üìö Core Architecture Concepts
Concept 1: CVIS Data Integration Philosophy
The Fundamental Distinction
PACS (Radiology)              CVIS (Cardiology)
‚îú‚îÄ Image storage              ‚îú‚îÄ Image storage
‚îú‚îÄ Image visualization        ‚îú‚îÄ Measurement data
‚îî‚îÄ Report management          ‚îú‚îÄ Waveform data
                              ‚îú‚îÄ Clinical context
                              ‚îú‚îÄ Longitudinal comparison
                              ‚îú‚îÄ Automated decision support
                              ‚îî‚îÄ Registry reporting

Key Difference: Cardiology emphasizes DATA FUSION over pure imaging
Clinical Reality Example:
An echo cardiologist needs:

Ultrasound images ‚úì
Ejection fraction (numeric)
Chamber dimensions (structured)
Valve assessment (coded observations)
Prior study comparison (longitudinal data)
HF diagnosis correlation (EHR integration)
CDS alert if EF ‚â§35% (automated insight)

A radiologist needs:

CT/MRI images ‚úì
Report availability ‚úì

Consultant Insight: Epic Cupid's limitations aren't technical failures‚Äîthey reflect Epic's core strength as enterprise system, not specialty data platform. This explains hybrid implementations.

